{"lemma":"حُكَّة","slug":"حُكَّة","root":"ح.ك.ك","root_slug":"ح-ك-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ك-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8664","n8671"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an itch","examples":[{"text":"أَنَا أُحِسُّ بِحِكَّةٍ فِي كَتِفِي.","english":"My shoulder is itchy."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a scab, anything one scratches"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mange, scabies"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lice","tags":["archaic"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħik.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8664","headword_ar":"حَكَّهُ","root":"Hk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~N","text_ar":"حَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He scratched, scraped, rubbed, grated, chafed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fretted, it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he scraped off, abraded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"otherwise removed, its superficial part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~N","text_ar":"حَكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scratching:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a body to pass upon another body with collision:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [as meaning scratching and the like,] it is with the nail, and with the hand, &c. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Hak~a ZahoriY mivolu yadiY","text_ar":"مَا حَكَّ ظَهْرِى مِثْلُ يَدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing has scratched my back like my hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., meaning that one should abstain from relying upon others: and the same meaning is intended in the following verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maA Hak~a jilodaka mivolu Zuforiko\n                      \n                     \n                        fataw~ala A^anota jamiyEa A^amoriko"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing has scratched thy skin like thy nail: so manage thou thyself all thine affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har pp. 432 et seq.) The saying, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA Hakakotu","text_ar":"اـِذَا حَكَكْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroHapF dam~ayotuhaA","text_ar":"قَرْحَةً دَمَّيْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When I scratch a sore, I make it bleed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when I desire an object, I attain it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~a fiY SadoriY","text_ar":"حَكَّ فِى صَدْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHk~","text_ar":"احكّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtk~","text_ar":"احتكّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the first whereof, which is mentioned by IDrd preceded by the negative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", is the most approved, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It wrought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operated, in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, my mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) said of a suggestion of the devil, that comes into one's mind. (TA.) Or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hak~a fiY Sadorihi ka*aA","text_ar":"حَكَّ فِى صَدْرِهِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a thing occurred to his mind as a thing outweighed in probability,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a matter of suspicion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Hak~a fiY SadoriY","text_ar":"مَا حَكَّ فِى صَدْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It did not make an impression upon my mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 648.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ivomu maA Hak~a","text_ar":"الاـِثْمُ مَا حَكَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Sadorika","text_ar":"فِى صَدْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sin is that which makes an impression upon thy mind, and induces a suspicion that it is an act of disobedience, because the mind is not dilated thereby."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAka","text_ar":"حَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwk","text_ar":"حوك"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hyk","text_ar":"حيك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haz~a","text_ar":"حَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Hak~a fiY SadoriY minohu $aYo'N","text_ar":"مَا حَكَّ فِى صَدْرِى مِنْهُ شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing thereof was unsettled, so as to be doubtful, in my mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Hak~a fiY SadoriY ka*aA","text_ar":"مَا حَكَّ فِى صَدْرِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a thing did not cause dilatation"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasure"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in my mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.)       -A2-  See also 8.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hakikati Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"حَكِكَتِ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, K,) a verb of an unusual form, with the reduplication distinct, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHiHato","text_ar":"لَحِحَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHiHato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"لَحِحَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beast had its hoof worn away at the edges."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","Mgh","K","KL","TA","Kr"]},{"entry_id":"n8671","headword_ar":"حِكَّةٌ","root":"Hk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An itching;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotak~a","text_ar":"اِحْتَكَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as used in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtk~ ArA^sY","text_ar":"احتكّ اراسى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HukaAkN","text_ar":"حُكَاكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jarab","text_ar":"جَرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or it differs from the latter; and is said to be the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jarab","text_ar":"جَرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that one scratches; as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jarab","text_ar":"جَرَب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [in the present day particularly applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain cutaneous disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said in the medical books to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thin humour, causing swelling, originating beneath the skin, not accompanied with pus, but with what resembles bran, and quick in passing away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  And hence (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lice."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hik~N","text_ar":"حِكٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","MF","Mgh"]}]}}